ACT:
 Constitution of India, 1950--Art. 371-D, cls. (3) and (5)-- Amending Power of Parliament--Exclusion of High Court's power of judicial review by an enactment--Not viola- tive of basic structure doctrine--If the enactment provides for an equally effective and efficacious alternative mecha- nism or authority for judicial review--Proviso to cl.
 (5)--Conferring power on State Government--To modify or annul final order of Administrative Tribunal--Held, viola- tive of basic structure doctrine, against concept of justice and principle of rule law--Held, ultra vires the amending power of Parliament--Main part of cl. (5), being closely inter-related with the proviso, held, also unconstitutional and void.
 Administrative Law: State Administrative Tribunal--Power conferred on government to modify or annul order of Tribu- nal--Held, violates rule of law as also basic structure doctrine and declared unconstitutional.
 
